      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scalar functions can have performance implications when used in large queries or within loops, as they are executed row-by-row. However, given the simplicity of this function, the performance impact is minimal when used appropriately. It is important to avoid using scalar functions in SELECT statements that process large datasets, as this can lead to performance bottlenecks."
